text:
The best beehoon Nasi Lemak I‚Äôve had! The chicken is so fresh and crispy, and the flavor of the chili is great. I was hesitant on ordering the luncheon meat because it looked dry, but turned out to be wonderful. I love their generosity of the luncheon meat cut too, most places are so thin and stingy these days.

Will def make this a go-to spot for beehoon!

Side note: the Teh here is really good toooooo.
Super good economic bee hoon!!!! Auntie also very generous with the chilli upon request. Always long queue here so do come earlier

$3.10 for fried noodles, an egg and a piece of luncheon meat.  Noodles are a bit salty.

Queue moves fast üëç

I haven't got to eat their nasi coz I forgot it is actually nasi lemak üòÖ
Will come back to eat again and decide whether to add the missing 1 star, coz their bee hoon is just so-so~

Their service though, damn awesome, despite the crowd
The sambal taste good with the coconut milk rice, generous portion comes with very affordable price. Do expect long queue during peak hours.
